---
import InnerPageLayout from '../layouts/InnerPageLayout.astro';
import SectionCTA from '../components/SectionCTA.astro';
---

<InnerPageLayout
  title="Who We Are — EnPraxis"
  description="EnPraxis builds the Empower AI platform — where intelligence becomes purposeful, trustworthy action. Learn about the philosophy, passion, and principles behind our work."
  heroLabel="Who We Are"
  heroTitle="Action Embodied in Intelligence"
  heroSubtitle="We believe the measure of intelligence isn't what a system knows — it's what it does. We built EnPraxis to turn knowledge into reliable, governed, purposeful action."
  heroImage="/images/pages/who-we-are/hero.png"
  ogImage="/images/pages/who-we-are/og.png"
>
  <!-- Section 1: The Name -->
  <section class="inner-section container">
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Why EnPraxis</h2>
        <p>Our name comes from two Ancient Greek roots:</p>
        <div class="etymology">
          <div class="etymology-term">
            <span class="greek">En-</span> <span class="origin">(&#7952;&#957;)</span>
            <p>"Within" or "embodied" &mdash; implying internalized, inherent qualities. From the same root as <em>enkrateia</em>, the Aristotelian virtue of rational self-mastery.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="etymology-term">
            <span class="greek">Praxis</span> <span class="origin">(&#960;&#961;&#940;&#958;&#953;&#962;)</span>
            <p>"Action," "deed," or "practice" &mdash; not merely doing, but <em>reasoned</em> doing. Aristotle distinguished praxis from mere production: it is ethical, purposeful action that bridges theory and practice.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>Combined, EnPraxis means <strong>"action from within"</strong> &mdash; embodied practice. It captures exactly what we build: AI agents that don't merely compute or plan, but embody epistemic strength to perform justified, self-governed deeds in complex environments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in">
        <div class="name-visual">
          <div class="name-assembled">
            <span class="name-prefix">En</span><span class="name-core">Praxis</span>
          </div>
          <div class="name-meaning">Action from Within</div>
          <div class="name-tagline">Where Knowledge Becomes Deed</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Our Belief -->
  <section class="inner-section alt-bg">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="prose">
          <h2>What We Believe</h2>
          <p>The AI industry is captivated by intelligence &mdash; bigger models, more parameters, higher benchmarks. We're captivated by something different: <strong>action</strong>.</p>
          <p>Intelligence without action is trivia. Action without intelligence is reckless. What enterprises actually need is the bridge: systems that internalize knowledge, reason about it with rigor, and then <em>act</em> &mdash; reliably, traceably, and under governance.</p>
          <p>That conviction shapes everything we build. We don't chase model size. We chase trustworthy execution. We don't optimize for impressive demos. We optimize for outcomes that survive audit, scale across teams, and compound over years.</p>
          <p>The world doesn't need another AI that can answer questions. It needs AI that can <span class="gradient-text">do the work</span> &mdash; and prove it did it right.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fade-in">
          <div class="belief-card">
            <blockquote>
              <p>"The distinction between theory and practice is not a distinction between knowing and doing. It is a distinction between two kinds of doing &mdash; one governed by reason, the other not."</p>
              <cite>&mdash; Aristotle, <em>Nicomachean Ethics</em></cite>
            </blockquote>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: What Drives Us -->
  <section class="inner-section container">
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>What Drives Us</h2>
        <p>We saw a gap that no one was closing.</p>
        <p>Regulated enterprises &mdash; healthcare, life sciences, financial services &mdash; were watching AI transform every industry around them. But the tools on offer asked them to trade governance for capability, or capability for compliance. The choice was always: move fast and break trust, or move slowly and fall behind.</p>
        <p>We refused to accept that tradeoff. We believed it was possible to build AI that acts autonomously <em>and</em> maintains complete traceability. That generates production code <em>and</em> produces deterministic, auditable output. That empowers domain experts <em>and</em> satisfies regulators.</p>
        <p>So we built the Empower platform &mdash; a semantic intelligence engine where business meaning is the source of truth, deterministic generators produce code without hallucination, and every action traces back to a specification that humans wrote and reviewed.</p>
        <p>We didn't build another AI tool. We built the infrastructure for <strong>trustworthy action at enterprise scale</strong>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in">
        <div class="drive-visual">
          <div class="drive-item">
            <div class="drive-rejected">Move fast, break trust</div>
            <div class="drive-x">&times;</div>
          </div>
          <div class="drive-item">
            <div class="drive-rejected">Move slowly, fall behind</div>
            <div class="drive-x">&times;</div>
          </div>
          <div class="drive-item chosen">
            <div class="drive-chosen">Move decisively, with governance</div>
            <div class="drive-check">&#10003;</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Our Principles -->
  <section class="inner-section alt-bg">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Our Principles</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">These aren't aspirations. They're engineering constraints we hold ourselves to every day.</p>

      <div class="principle-cards">
        <div class="principle-card fade-in">
          <div class="principle-header"><span class="principle-icon">&#9670;</span><h3>Embodied Action</h3></div>
          <p>Intelligence that doesn't act is incomplete. Every capability we build is measured by what it enables people and systems to <em>do</em> &mdash; not what it can discuss.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="principle-card fade-in">
          <div class="principle-header"><span class="principle-icon">&#9670;</span><h3>Epistemic Trust</h3></div>
          <p>If a system can't explain how it reached a conclusion, it shouldn't be making decisions. We build AI with justified beliefs &mdash; grounded in formal semantics, traceable through every layer.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="principle-card fade-in">
          <div class="principle-header"><span class="principle-icon">&#9670;</span><h3>Semantic Grounding</h3></div>
          <p>Meaning isn't a prompt. It's a formal, version-controlled specification that machines can reason about and humans can review. We ground every action in domain semantics, not statistical patterns.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="principle-card fade-in">
          <div class="principle-header"><span class="principle-icon">&#9670;</span><h3>Purposeful Autonomy</h3></div>
          <p>Autonomy without governance is chaos. We give agents the ability to act independently &mdash; within policy boundaries that humans define, audit, and evolve. Self-mastery, not self-direction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: The Name in Practice -->
  <section class="inner-section container">
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>The Name in Practice</h2>
        <p>EnPraxis isn't just a name. It's a design philosophy.</p>
        <p>Every feature we ship, every architecture decision we make, every customer engagement we run &mdash; we ask: <em>Does this enable trustworthy action?</em> Does it make the system more capable of acting from internalized knowledge, under governance, with full traceability?</p>
        <p>The Empower platform is where EnPraxis becomes real &mdash; where semantic specifications become production code, where business intent becomes system behavior, where knowledge becomes deed.</p>
        <p>In the 2026 landscape of agentic AI, execution matters more than raw intelligence, and trustworthiness is the key to enterprise adoption. That's why we exist. That's what drives us every day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="fade-in">
        <div class="practice-visual">
          <div class="practice-step">
            <div class="practice-label">Knowledge</div>
            <div class="practice-desc">Domain semantics, formal specifications</div>
          </div>
          <div class="practice-arrow">&darr;</div>
          <div class="practice-step">
            <div class="practice-label">Internalization</div>
            <div class="practice-desc">Epistemic grounding, validated models</div>
          </div>
          <div class="practice-arrow">&darr;</div>
          <div class="practice-step highlight-step">
            <div class="practice-label">Action</div>
            <div class="practice-desc">Governed, traceable, trustworthy execution</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SectionCTA
    title="Interested in what we're building?"
    subtitle="See how EnPraxis turns knowledge into trustworthy action through the Empower platform."
    secondaryText="Explore the Platform"
    secondaryHref="/platform/"
  />

</InnerPageLayout>

<style>
  /* Etymology */
  .etymology {
    margin: 2rem 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .etymology-term {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-card);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(50, 69, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .greek {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-1), var(--color-accent-2));
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .origin {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  .etymology-term p {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Name visual */
  .name-visual {
    background: var(--color-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(50, 69, 255, 0.2);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: 300px;
  }

  .name-assembled {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .name-prefix {
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
  }

  .name-core {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-1), var(--color-accent-2));
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .name-meaning {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
  }

  .name-tagline {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Belief card */
  .belief-card {
    background: var(--color-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(50, 69, 255, 0.2);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 300px;
  }

  .belief-card blockquote {
    margin: 0;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent-1);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .belief-card blockquote p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .belief-card cite {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  /* Gradient text */
  .gradient-text {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-1), var(--color-accent-2));
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Drive visual */
  .drive-visual {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .drive-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.2);
  }

  .drive-item.chosen {
    background: rgba(0, 230, 180, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 230, 180, 0.3);
  }

  .drive-rejected {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    text-decoration: line-through;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .drive-x {
    color: #ff6b6b;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .drive-chosen {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .drive-check {
    color: #00e6b4;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Section intro */
  .section-intro {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* Principle cards */
  .principle-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .principle-card {
    background: var(--color-card);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(50, 69, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .principle-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .principle-icon {
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .principle-card h3 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .principle-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* Practice visual */
  .practice-visual {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .practice-step {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--color-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(50, 69, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .practice-step.highlight-step {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(50, 69, 255, 0.12), rgba(188, 82, 238, 0.12));
    border-color: rgba(50, 69, 255, 0.35);
  }

  .practice-label {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .highlight-step .practice-label {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-1), var(--color-accent-2));
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .practice-desc {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .practice-arrow {
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .name-assembled {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .name-meaning {
      font-size: 1rem;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .principle-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
